<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>lay of the land • lay the land</xh5><p> <i>lay of the land</i>—(also: lie of the land) the state of affairs: I think my success was due to my waiting and not rushing in before I saw the <u>lay of the land</u>.</p><p> <i>lay the land</i>—(Nautical) sail out to such a distance as to lose sight of land: We found ourselves to be at the distance of seven leagues to the westward of the island. About noon that day we had <u>laid the land</u>.</p> </entry>
